0.1 CARTE DE VOTE

Nous allons dans un premier temps importer les donnes ncssaire la gnration de cette premire carte.

library(linemap)
library(sf)
## Linking to GEOS 3.9.1, GDAL 3.4.0, PROJ 8.1.1; sf_use_s2() is TRUE
library(mapsf)
data <- st_read("vote.gpkg", "jointure")
## Reading layer `jointure' from data source 
##   `/Users/savannahlaurent/Desktop/SIG/PROJET FINAL/script/vote.gpkg' 
##   using driver `GPKG'
## Simple feature collection with 32 features and 18 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 661088.1 ymin: 6865338 xmax: 663354.7 ymax: 6869043
## Projected CRS: RGF93 / Lambert-93
seuils <- c(0,25, 50, 75, 100, 125, 150, 175, 200, 300)
palette <- mf_get_pal(n = c(5,2), pal = c("Mint", "Burg"))
hist(data$txVotants, border = NA, breaks = seuils, right = F, col=palette, main = "", xlab = "", ylab="")

mf_map(data,  var = "txVotants", breaks = seuils, pal = palette,border = NA, leg_pos = "n")
## Please use the 'type' argument to map variables.
mf_label(data, "txVotants")

par(mar = c(2,2,2,2))


## CARTE INSEE

Nous pouvons gnrer une carte du carroyage de la ville de Bondy grce  la fonction : mf_map


```r
library(mapsf)
data <- st_read("insee.gpkg", "bondy")
## Reading layer `bondy' from data source 
##   `/Users/savannahlaurent/Desktop/SIG/PROJET FINAL/script/insee.gpkg' 
##   using driver `GPKG'
## Simple feature collection with 188 features and 42 fields
## Geometry type: POLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 661088.1 ymin: 6865338 xmax: 663354.7 ymax: 6869043
## Projected CRS: RGF93 / Lambert-93
mf_map(data, type = "choro", pal = "Burg",
       border = NA, var = "Men_pauv", leg_title = "Nb de mnages pauvres")
mf_layout(title =  "Pauvret  Bondy", credits = "INSEE Carroyage 200 m")

```
